    return "This is a code block"
```
```

### Tables

```markdown
| Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 |
|----------|----------|----------|
| Value 1  | Value 2  | Value 3  |
```

## Implementation Notes

When generating markdown files:

1. Start with a level 1 heading
2. Use proper indentation (2 spaces)
3. Include language specifiers for code blocks
4. Maintain consistent line spacing
5. Follow list formatting rules
6. Respect line length limits (except for code and tables)
7. Use allowed HTML elements only when necessary
8. Include proper spacing around headers and lists

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

- Mixing header styles
- Inconsistent list indentation
- Missing code block language specifiers
- Excessive blank lines
- Improper HTML usage
- Trailing whitespace
- Missing spaces after list markers
- Duplicate headers in the same section

 